  "english": [
    "if she took a vow when she was <b>a young woman who had not</b> yet <b>reached her majority, and she is an orphan;</b> if she took a vow when she was <b>a grown woman and her father died;</b> if she took a vow when she was <b>a young woman,</b> and she became <b>a grown woman, and her father died;</b> if she took a vow when she was <b>a young woman who had not reached her majority, and her father died;</b> if she took a vow when she was <b>a young woman, and her father died, and after her father died she reached her majority;</b> if she took a vow when she was <b>a grown woman and her father is</b> still <b>alive;</b> and if she took a vow when she was <b>a young woman,</b> and she became <b>a grown woman, and her father is</b> still <b>alive. Rabbi Yehuda says:</b> With regard to <b>even one who married off his minor daughter, and she was widowed or divorced and she returned to him,</b> and according to her age <b>she still</b> is in the category of <b>a young woman,</b> her vows cannot be nullified.",
    "<strong>GEMARA:</strong> <b>Rav Yehuda said</b> that <b>Rav said: This</b> mishna is <b>the statement of Rabbi Yehuda,</b> who spelled out all the cases and listed nine young women whose vows are upheld. <b>But the Rabbis say</b> that it is unnecessary to go into such detail. Instead, they simply said: There are <b>three young women whose vows are upheld</b> and cannot be nullified: <b>A grown woman, and an orphan, and an orphan in her father’s lifetime,</b> i.e., a young woman who was divorced or widowed while her father was still alive and is considered an orphan in that her father no longer has jurisdiction over her.",
    "<strong>MISHNA:</strong> If a woman said to her husband: <b>Deriving benefit from</b> my <b>father or from your father is <i>konam</i> for me if I</b> will <b>prepare</b> anything <b>for you;</b> or if she said: <b>Deriving benefit from you</b> is <i>konam</i> <b>for me if I</b> will <b>prepare</b> anything <b>for</b> my <b>father or for your father,</b> the husband <b>can nullify</b> this vow.",
    "<strong>GEMARA:</strong> <b>It is taught</b> in a <i>baraita</i>: If a woman said to her husband: <b>Deriving benefit from</b> my <b>father or from your father</b> is <i>konam</i> <b>for me if I</b> will <b>prepare</b> anything <b>for you, Rabbi Natan says</b> her husband <b>cannot nullify</b> the vow. She must prepare food for him, as she is obligated to do so by virtue of their being married, and it is prohibited for her to benefit from their respective fathers. The husband cannot nullify a vow that has not yet taken effect and that depends on the fulfillment of a certain condition. <b>And the Rabbis say</b> that even in such a case <b>he can nullify</b> her vow.",
    "The <i>baraita</i> continues: If the woman said to her husband: <b>I am removed from the Jews,</b> i.e., the benefit of my engaging in sexual intercourse will be forbidden to all Jews, <b>if I engage in sexual intercourse with you, Rabbi Natan says he cannot nullify</b> the vow. Rather, she must engage in sexual intercourse with her husband, as she is obligated to do so by virtue of their marriage, and she will be forbidden to all other Jews. <b>And the Rabbis say he can nullify</b> her vow.",
    "§ It is related that there was <b>a certain man who</b> took a vow that all <b>benefit from the world should be forbidden to him if</b> he <b>marries a woman when he has not</b> yet <b>learned <i>halakha</i>. He would run up a ladder and rope but was not able to learn</b> the material, i.e., despite all his efforts he failed in his studies. <b>Rav Aḥa bar Rav Huna came and misled him,</b> allowing him to understand that even if he took a vow, the vow would not take effect, <b>and</b> so <b>he married a woman.</b>"
  ],
  "gemara": [
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "<span class=\"sentence\" id=\"0\" type=\"start\">&star;</span>נַעֲרָה שֶׁלֹּא בָּגְרָה וְהִיא יְתוֹמָה. בּוֹגֶרֶת וּמֵת",
      "segment_ids": [
        0
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "אָבִיהָ. נַעֲרָה בּוֹגֶרֶת וּמֵת אָבִיהָ. נַעֲרָה שֶׁלֹּא",
      "segment_ids": [
        0
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "בָּגְרָה וּמֵת אָבִיהָ. נַעֲרָה שֶׁמֵּת אָבִיהָ וּמִשֶּׁמֵּת",
      "segment_ids": [
        0
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "אָבִיהָ בָּגְרָה. בּוֹגֶרֶת וְאָבִיהָ קַיָּים. נַעֲרָה בּוֹגֶרֶת",
      "segment_ids": [
        0
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "וְאָבִיהָ קַיָּים. <span class=\"name-reference-marker name-reference-tanna\" data-sage-type=\"tanna\" title=\"Rabbi Yehuda bar Rabbi Elai, fifth-generation Tanna\" data-authority-id=\"1395\" data-full-name=\"Rabbi Yehuda bar Rabbi Elai\" data-name-he=\"רבי יהודה ברבי אילעאי\">רַבִּי יְהוּדָה</span> אוֹמֵר: אַף הַמַּשִּׂיא בִּתּוֹ",
      "segment_ids": [
        0
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "הַקְּטַנָּה וְנִתְאַלְמְנָה אוֹ נִתְגָּרְשָׁה וְחָזְרָה אֶצְלוֹ —",
      "segment_ids": [
        0
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "עֲדַיִין הִיא נַעֲרָה.<span class=\"sugya-marker sugya-marker-vilna-piska\" data-sugya-kind=\"vilna-piska\" data-sugya-id=\"295\" data-raw-symbol=\"׃\">׃</span> <span class=\"sentence\" id=\"1\" type=\"start\">&star;</span><big><strong>גְּמָ׳</strong></big> אָמַר <span class=\"name-reference-marker name-reference-amora\" data-sage-type=\"amora\" title=\"Rav Yehuda bar Yeḥezkel, second-generation Amora\" data-authority-id=\"1394\" data-full-name=\"Rav Yehuda bar Yeḥezkel\" data-name-he=\"רב יהודה בר יחזקאל\">רַב יְהוּדָה</span> אָמַר <span class=\"name-reference-marker name-reference-amora\" data-sage-type=\"amora\" title=\"of Rav, first-generation Amora\" data-authority-id=\"2578\" data-full-name=\"of Rav\" data-name-he=\"רב\">רַב</span>: זוֹ",
      "segment_ids": [
        1
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "דִּבְרֵי <span class=\"name-reference-marker name-reference-tanna\" data-sage-type=\"tanna\" title=\"Rabbi Yehuda bar Rabbi Elai, fifth-generation Tanna\" data-authority-id=\"1395\" data-full-name=\"Rabbi Yehuda bar Rabbi Elai\" data-name-he=\"רבי יהודה ברבי אילעאי\">רַבִּי יְהוּדָה</span>. אֲבָל חֲכָמִים אוֹמְרִים, שָׁלֹשׁ נְעָרוֹת",
      "segment_ids": [
        1
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "נִדְרֵיהֶן קַיָּימִין: בּוֹגֶרֶת, וִיתוֹמָה, וִיתוֹמָה בְּחַיֵּי",
      "segment_ids": [
        1
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "הָאָב.<span class=\"sugya-marker sugya-marker-vilna-piska\" data-sugya-kind=\"vilna-piska\" data-sugya-id=\"296\" data-raw-symbol=\"׃\">׃</span> <span class=\"sentence\" id=\"2\" type=\"start\">&star;</span><big><strong>מַתְנִי׳</strong></big> ״קֻוֽנָּם שֶׁאֵינִי נֶהֱנֶה <span class=\"name-reference-marker name-reference-amora\" data-sage-type=\"amora\" title=\"of Rav, first-generation Amora\" data-authority-id=\"2578\" data-full-name=\"of Rav\" data-name-he=\"רב\">לְאַבָּא</span>",
      "segment_ids": [
        2
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "וּלְאָבִיךָ אִם עוֹשָׂה אֲנִי עַל פִּיךָ״, ״שֶׁאֵינִי נֶהֱנֵית",
      "segment_ids": [
        2
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "לְךָ אִם עוֹשָׂה אֲנִי עַל פִּי <span class=\"name-reference-marker name-reference-amora\" data-sage-type=\"amora\" title=\"of Rav, first-generation Amora\" data-authority-id=\"2578\" data-full-name=\"of Rav\" data-name-he=\"רב\">אַבָּא</span> וְעַל פִּי אָבִיךָ״ —",
      "segment_ids": [
        2
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "הֲרֵי זֶה יָפֵר.<span class=\"sugya-marker sugya-marker-vilna-piska\" data-sugya-kind=\"vilna-piska\" data-sugya-id=\"297\" data-raw-symbol=\"׃\">׃</span> <span class=\"sentence\" id=\"3\" type=\"start\">&star;</span><big><strong>גְּמָ׳</strong></big> תַּנְיָא: ״שֶׁאֵינִי נֶהֱנֵית <span class=\"name-reference-marker name-reference-amora\" data-sage-type=\"amora\" title=\"of Rav, first-generation Amora\" data-authority-id=\"2578\" data-full-name=\"of Rav\" data-name-he=\"רב\">לְאַבָּא</span>",
      "segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "וּלְאָבִיךְ אִם אֲנִי עוֹשָׂה לְפִיךָ״, <span class=\"name-reference-marker name-reference-tanna\" data-sage-type=\"tanna\" title=\"Rabbi Natan I, fifth and sixth-generation Tanna\" data-authority-id=\"2330\" data-full-name=\"Rabbi Natan I\" data-name-he=\"רבי נתן\">רַבִּי נָתָן</span> אוֹמֵר: לֹא",
      "segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "יָפֵר. וַחֲכָמִים אוֹמְרִים: יָפֵר. <span class=\"sentence\" id=\"4\" type=\"start\">&star;</span>״נְטוּלָה אֲנִי מִן הַיְּהוּדִים אִם",
      "segment_ids": [
        4
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "מְשַׁמַּשְׁתֶּךָ״, <span class=\"name-reference-marker name-reference-tanna\" data-sage-type=\"tanna\" title=\"Rabbi Natan I, fifth and sixth-generation Tanna\" data-authority-id=\"2330\" data-full-name=\"Rabbi Natan I\" data-name-he=\"רבי נתן\">רַבִּי נָתָן</span> אוֹמֵר: לֹא יָפֵר. וַחֲכָמִים אוֹמְרִים: יָפֵר. <span class=\"sugya-marker sugya-marker-steinsaltz\" data-sugya-kind=\"steinsaltz\" data-sugya-id=\"105\" data-sentence-id=\"5\">§</span> <span class=\"sentence\" id=\"5\" type=\"start\">&star;</span>הָהוּא",
      "segment_ids": [
        5
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "גַּבְרָא דְּאִיתְּסַר הֲנָיָיתָא דְּעָלְמָא עֲלֵיהּ אִי נָסֵיב",
      "segment_ids": [
        5
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "אִיתְּתָא כִּי לָא תָּנֵינָא הִילְכְתָא. רָהֵיט בְּגַפָּא",
      "segment_ids": [
        5
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "וְתוּבַלְיָא וְלָא אִמְּצִי לְמִיתְנֵא. אֲתָא <span class=\"name-reference-marker name-reference-unknown\" data-sage-type=\"unknown\" title=\"Rav Aḥa bar Rav Huna\" data-authority-id=\"20780\" data-full-name=\"Rav Aḥa bar Rav Huna\" data-name-he=\"רב אחא בר רב הונא\" data-crossline-group=\"name-ref-crossline-53924\">רַב אַחָא</span>",
      "segment_ids": [
        5
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "<span class=\"name-reference-marker name-reference-unknown\" data-sage-type=\"unknown\" title=\"Rav Aḥa bar Rav Huna\" data-authority-id=\"20780\" data-full-name=\"Rav Aḥa bar Rav Huna\" data-name-he=\"רב אחא בר רב הונא\" data-crossline-group=\"name-ref-crossline-53924\">בַּר רַב הוּנָא</span> וְשַׁבְּשֵׁיהּ וְאִינְּסִיב אִיתְּתָא,",
      "segment_ids": [
        5
      ]
    }
  ],
  "rashi": [
    {
      "width": "450px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "<b>נַעֲרָה שֶׁלֹּא בָּגְרָה וְהִיא יְתוֹמָה. בּוֹגֶרֶת וּמֵת אָבִיהָ. נַעֲרָה בּוֹגֶרֶת וּמֵת</b>",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 89b:1:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        0
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "450px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "<b>אָבִיהָ. <span class=\"dh-divergent\">ונערה</span> שֶׁמֵּת אָבִיהָ וּמִשֶּׁמֵּת אָבִיהָ בָּגְרָה. בּוֹגֶרֶת וְאָבִיהָ</b>",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 89b:1:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        0
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "450px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "<b>קַיָּים. <span class=\"dh-divergent\">ר&#x27;</span> יְהוּדָה אוֹמֵר: <span class=\"dh-divergent\">כו&#x27;</span>.</b> בוגרת והיא יתומה בשעת הנדר היתה",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 89b:1:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        0
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "450px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "בוגרת וכבר היתה יתומה מבעלה כלומר יתומה דמתניתין יתומה",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 89b:1:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        0
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "בחיי האב כדמפרשי רבנן בגמ'",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 89b:1:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        0
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "דיתומה דשייך למימר בבעל כבאב",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 89b:1:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        0
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "דיקא נמי היכא דתני מיתת האב תני",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 89b:1:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        0
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "לה בפירוש בוגרת ומת אביה:",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 89b:1:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        0
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "<b>גְּמָ׳ <span class=\"dh-divergent\">זו</span> <span class=\"dh-divergent\">דיבר</span> <span class=\"dh-divergent\">ר&#x27;</span> <span class=\"dh-divergent\">יהודיה</span></b> דקתני",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 89b:2:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        0
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "תשע: <b>אֲבָל חֲכָמִים אוֹמְרִים, שָׁלֹשׁ</b>",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 89b:2:2",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        0
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "<b>נְעָרוֹת נִדְרֵיהֶן קַיָּימִין: בּוֹגֶרֶת, וִיתוֹמָה</b>",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 89b:2:2",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        0
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "<b>וִיתוֹמָה בְּחַיֵּי הָאָב</b> וכולהו תשע",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 89b:2:2",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        0
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "דמתני' נכללות בהני שלש: <b>מַתְנִי׳</b>",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 89b:3:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        1
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "<b>״קֻוֽנָּם שֶׁאֵינִי <span class=\"dh-divergent\">עושה</span> לְאַבָּא וּלְאָבִיךָ.</b>",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 89b:3:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        1
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "כלומר שאני נותן להם יהא עליהם",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 89b:3:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        1
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "קונם: <b>הֲרֵי זֶה <span class=\"dh-divergent\">יכול</span> <span class=\"dh-divergent\">להפר</span>.</b> אע\"ג",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 89b:3:2",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        1
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "דלאו נדרי עינוי נפש אינון דלאו כל",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 89b:3:2",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        1
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "כמיניה לאפקועי שיעבודא מינה אפי'",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 89b:3:2",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        1
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "הכי דברים שבינו לבינה הויין ויכול",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 89b:3:2",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        1
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "להפר כלומר הרשות בידו: <b>גְּמָ׳ <span class=\"dh-divergent\">ר&#x27;</span></b>",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 89b:4:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        1
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "<b><span class=\"dh-divergent\">נתן</span> אוֹמֵר: <span class=\"dh-divergent\">לא</span> <span class=\"dh-divergent\">יפר</span>.</b> דקסבר הואיל",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 89b:4:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        1
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "ועדיין לא חל הנדר שכל זמן שלא",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 89b:4:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        1
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "עשתה לפי בעלה ולא שימשתו אינה",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 89b:4:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        1
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "אסורה לאביה ולאביו ולא יפר:",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 89b:4:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        1
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "<b><span class=\"dh-divergent\">וחכ&quot;א</span> יָפֵר</b> אע\"פ שעדיין לא חל",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 89b:4:2",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        1
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "הנדר עליה: <b>הָהוּא גַּבְרָא <span class=\"dh-divergent\">דיאמר</span></b>",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 89b:6:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        4
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "<b><span class=\"dh-divergent\">תיתסר</span> הֲנָיָיתָא דְּעָלְמָא עֲלֵיהּ אִי</b>",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 89b:6:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        4
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "<b>נָסֵיב אִיתְּתָא כִּי לָא תָּנֵינָא <span class=\"dh-divergent\">הלכתא</span>.</b>",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 89b:6:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        4
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "כלומר תיתסר הנאת עולם עלי אם",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 89b:6:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        4
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "450px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "אקח אשה עד שאשנה הלכות: <b>רָהֵיט בְּגַפָּא וְתוּבַלְיָא.</b> גפא קרי",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 89b:6:2",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        4
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "450px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "סולם שעולין בו באילן תובליא חבל שתולין בדקל ומושכין להם",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 89b:6:2",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        4
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "450px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "למטה הענפים שבהן התמרים ומשל של בני אדם הוא רץ למעלה",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 89b:6:2",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        4
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "450px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "ולמטה לעסוק ולשנות הלכות ולא איסתייעא מילתא ואית דמפרש",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 89b:6:2",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        4
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "450px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "דהיינו בכפא רץ יחידי למעלה ולמטה כאדם שעולה בחבל באילן:",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 89b:6:2",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        4
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "450px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "<b><span class=\"dh-divergent\">תובליא</span>.</b> חבל כדאמרי' בבבא בתרא (<a href=\"/bava_batra/33b\">דף לג:</a>) מאן דנקט מגליא",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 89b:6:3",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        4
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "450px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "ותובליא ואמר אזיל ואגזור דיקלא דפלניא: ושבשיה ואנסביה איתתא",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Nedarim 89b:6:3",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        4
      ]
    }
  ],
